Package: inf.ranger
Type: Package
Title: Inference Forest Extensions to Ranger Random Forests
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-03-13
Authors@R: c(
    person("Nathaniel S.", "O'Connell", email = "nathaniel.oconnell@wfusm.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Marvin N.", "Wright", role = "aut", comment = "Original ranger package"))
Description: A modified version of the ranger random forest package that adds 
    standardized splitting criteria and softmax variable selection for use with 
    the inference forest framework of O'Connell (2026). Includes corrections for 
    balance advantage and search advantage in split selection, enabling fair 
    comparison of binary and continuous candidate variables. All original ranger 
    functionality is preserved. Based on ranger by Wright and Ziegler (2017).
License: GPL-3
Imports: Rcpp (>= 0.11.2), Matrix
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppEigen
Depends: R (>= 3.1)
Suggests: 
    survival,
    testthat
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
URL: https://github.com/NateOConnellPhD/inf.ranger
BugReports: https://github.com/NateOConnellPhD/inf.ranger/issues
